Python:
mat = [
  [1, 2, 3],
  [4, 5, 6]
] 

👉 Access:

mat[row][col]

5️⃣ Types of Matrices (Only What You NEED)
🔹 Row Matrix

1 row, many columns

1 2 3
to write in loops for rows
for j in range(len(mat)):
 
🔹 Column Matrix
  for j in range(len(mat[0])): # column index
Many rows, 1 column

1
2
3

🔹 Square Matrix

Rows = Columns

1 2
3 4

🔹 Identity Matrix

Diagonal = 1, rest = 0

1 0
0 1

🔹 Zero Matrix

All elements = 0

👉 In coding interviews:

Square matrix is MOST common

6️⃣ Basic Matrix Operations (Must Know)
Operation	Meaning
Traversal	Visit each element
Row-wise	Row by row
Column-wise	Column by column
Diagonal	i == j
Transpose	Swap rows & columns
Sum	Row / column / diagonal sum

